Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
clonePtnObj(25.10)                                          clonePtnObj(25.10)

Name
       clonePtnObj - Syncs up the changes made to the specified objects in the
       master  or  clone  partitions in the design with other hierarchical in-
       stances (master and clones) of the same module

Syntax
       clonePtnObj

       [-help]

       [-checkOnly]

       [-objs {all busGuides specialWires}]

       [-redo]

       [-refHinsts <list_of_hinst_names>]

       [-skipCreateNewPartitionPorts]

       [-sync]

       [-targetHinsts <list_of_hinst_names>]

       [-undo]

       Syncs up the changes made to the specified objects  in  the  master  or
       clone  partitions in the design with other hierarchical instances (mas-
       ter and clones) of the same module.

Parameters
       -checkOnly
              When specified, the tool checks if the master and  clone  parti-
              tions are out of sync or not.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each clonePtnObj parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man clonePtnObj

       -objs {all busGuides specialWires}
              When specified, the tool does the sync-up of the  specified  ob-
              jects between master or clone partitions.

              * all: Synchronizes all objects.

              * busGuide: Synchronizes bus guide objects.

              * specialWires: Synchronizes special wires

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -redo  When  specified, the changes made to the object are done again .
              The master and clone partitions are brought to the next  commit-
              ted sync state.

              Note:  Currently  this parameter only supports the busGuides ob-
              ject type (-objs).

              Note: This parameter is exclusive with the -refHinsts and  -tar-
              getHinsts parameter options.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -refHinsts <list_of_hinst_names>
              Specifies  the name of the master or clone hierarchical instance
              from which the obj data is to be copied.

              Default: All master partitions in the design.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -skipCreateNewPartitionPorts
              Specifies that the creation of new partition ports for top-level
              nets that pass through partitions  is  skipped  during  sync-up.
              This helps to control port creation for special wires.

              Note: This parameter can only be used when the specialWires  ob-
              ject type is specified for the -objs parameter.

              Note:  When  the  -skipCreateNewPartitionPorts  parameter is not
              specified, new partition ports are created by default  for  top-
              level nets that pass through partitions.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -sync  When  specified,  the objects in all master and clone partitions
              are synced up by looking at the changes in shape in any  hierar-
              chical instance of the master and clone partitions.

              Note:  Currently  this parameter only supports the busGuides ob-
              ject type (-objs).

              Note: This parameter is exclusive with the -refHinsts and  -tar-
              getHinsts parameter options.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -targetHinsts <list_of_hinst_names>
              Specifies  the name of the master or clone hierarchical instance
              to which the obj data is to be copied.

              * When a master partition is specified with  the   -targetHinsts
                parameter,  specifying  the  -refHinsts becomes mandatory as a
                user provided hinst is considered to sync up objects.

              * When clones partitions are specified with  the   -targetHinsts
                parameter,  specifying  the   -refHinsts is optional as master
                hierarchical instances are automatically considered  (default)
                to sync-up objects

              Default: All clone partitions in the design.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -undo  When specified, the changes made to the object are reverted. The
              master  and  clone  partitions are brought to the last committed
              sync state.

              Note: Currently this parameter only supports the  busGuides  ob-
              ject type (-objs).

              Note:  This parameter is exclusive with the -refHinsts and -tar-
              getHinsts parameter options.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
       Hinst: A1 (master), A2 (clone), A3(clone), A4 (clone)

       Hinst: B1 (master), B2 (clone), B3(clone), B4 (clone)

              * The following commands syncs all clones  to  their  respective
                master.

                clonePtnObj

              * The  following  command syncs the hinsts A2 and A3 (clones) to
                the master of module A (A1).

                clonePtnObj -targetHinsts {A2 A3}

              * The following command syncs the  hinsts  A1  (master)  and  A3
                (clone) to the hinst A2 (clone)

                clonePtnObj -targetHinsts {A1 A3} -refHinsts {A2}

              * The following command syncs the hinsts A1 (master), A3, B2, B3
                (clones) to hinsts A2 (clone) and the master of module B (B1)

                clonePtnObj -targetHinsts {A1 A3 B2 B3} -refHinsts {A2}

              * The following command checks and reports if the hinsts A1(mas-
                ter)  and  A3,  B2, B3 (clones) are synced to hinst A2 (clone)
                and the master of module B (B1)

                clonePtnObj  -targetHinsts  {A1  A3  B2  B3}  -refHinsts  {A2}
                -checkOnly

              * The  following  command  checks  and  reports if the hinsts A1
                (master) and A3, B2,  B3  (clones)  are  synced  to  hinst  A2
                (clone) and the master of module B (B1) for bus guides only.

                clonePtnObj  -targetHinsts  {A1  A3  B2  B3}  -refHinsts  {A2}
                -checkOnly -objs {busGuides}

              * The following command syncs the hinsts A1 (master) and A3, B2,
                B3 (clones) to hinst A2 (clone) and the  master  of  module  B
                (B1) for bus guides only.

                clonePtnObj  -targetHinsts {A1 A3 B2 B3} -refHinsts {A2} -objs
                {busGuides}

